('Cost and Quality Report – Side By Side Display','"<ReportManifest xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" Id="0" Name="Cost and Quality Report – Side By Side Display" RptId="7D841284-5179-44E5-A00E-BDD042B0A7BD" ShowInterpretationText="true" Category="Quality" IsTrending="false" PreviewImage="CostAndQualityReport.png" ConsumerPreviewImage="ConsumerCostAndQuality.png" RequiresCmsProviderId="true" RequiresCostToChargeRatio="false"><IsChanged>true</IsChanged><IsDeleted>false</IsDeleted><SkipAudit>false</SkipAudit><Audiences><Audience AudienceType="Consumers" /></Audiences><InterpretationText>&lt;p&gt;For this topic, Hip Replacement Surgery, there is information you can use to compare hospitals on three related issues:  the quality of hip replacement surgery, the average cost of such a surgery, and how many patients get this surgery each year.  Ideally, look for a hospital with high quality ratings, a low average cost that performs hip replacement surgery on more patients each year.&lt;/p&gt;</InterpretationText><ReportAttributes>HospitalFilters</ReportAttributes><IconSets /><Filters /><Datasets><Dataset Name="Inpatient Discharge" /><Dataset Name="AHRQ-QI Provider Data" /></Datasets><Columns /></ReportManifest>"'),
