('Physician Profile','"<ReportManifest xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" Id="0" Name="Physician Profile" RptId="4C5727B4-0E85-4F80-ADE9-418B49A1373E" ShowInterpretationText="true" Category="Utilization" IsTrending="false" PreviewImage="PhysicianProfile - MQ60.jpg" ConsumerPreviewImage="ConsumerDoctorProfile_GeneralInformation.png" RequiresCmsProviderId="false" RequiresCostToChargeRatio="false"><IsChanged>true</IsChanged><IsDeleted>false</IsDeleted><SkipAudit>false</SkipAudit><Audiences><Audience AudienceType="Professionals" /><Audience AudienceType="Consumers" /></Audiences><InterpretationText>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ASSIGNMENT/PARTICIPATION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Accepts Medicare Assignment:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp; If Yes, then this physician is willing to accept the Medicare allowable charge for his/her services as payment in full.&amp;nbsp; If No, then you will be responsible for paying what the physicians charges, even if it is higher than the Medicare allowable charge.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Participation in Electronic Prescribing program:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Doctors can write a prescription for Medicare patients and send it electronically to participating pharmacies for the patient to pick up. Patients do not need to bring a written prescription on a piece of paper from their doctor in order to pick up their medication.&amp;rdquo;Yes&amp;rdquo; means this doctor participates in this program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Participation in Physician Quality Reporting System: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Doctors, or the medical group practice they belong to, voluntarily report information to the Physician Quality Reporting System about the quality of care they provide to their Medicare patients (for example, the number of their patients with diabetes who had well-controlled blood sugar levels).&amp;nbsp;&amp;rdquo;Yes&amp;rdquo; means this doctor participates in this program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Participation in Electronic Health Records program:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Doctors, or the hospitals they practice at, can use electronic health records to document a Medicare patient&amp;rsquo;s medical history. Electronic health records can help doctors make decisions about the kind of care a patient should receive.&amp;rdquo;Yes&amp;rdquo; means this doctor participates in this program.&lt;/p&gt;
</InterpretationText><ReportAttributes>Display</ReportAttributes><IconSets /><Filters><Filter Type="Display"><Values><FilterValue Name="Basic Descriptive Data" /><FilterValue Name="Map" /><FilterValue Name="Affiliated Hospitals" /></Values></Filter></Filters><Datasets><Dataset Name="Physician Data" /></Datasets><Columns /></ReportManifest>"'),
('Region Rates Report','"<ReportManifest xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" Id="0" Name="Region Rates Report" RptId="3a40cf6b-37ad-4861-b272-930ddf2b8802" ShowInterpretationText="true" Category="Utilization" IsTrending="false" PreviewImage="RegionRates.PNG" ConsumerPreviewImage="" RequiresCmsProviderId="false" RequiresCostToChargeRatio="true"><IsChanged>true</IsChanged><IsDeleted>false</IsDeleted><SkipAudit>false</SkipAudit><Audiences><Audience AudienceType="Professionals" /></Audiences><InterpretationText>&lt;P&gt;What are region rates of hospital use?&lt;/P&gt;	
	&lt;p&gt;Information is provided for each selected region by condition or procedure grouping. Select the titles in the top row to sort the results. Tables may include the following:&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Total US&lt;/b&gt;: National numbers are weighted estimates from the &lt;a href="http://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/" target="_blank"&gt;HCUP Nationwide Inpatient Sample&lt;/a&gt; (NIS), 2011, Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality (AHRQ).&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Total US region&lt;/b&gt;: Regional categories are defined by the Census Bureau: Midwest, Northeast, South, and West. Numbers for each region are weighted estimates from the &lt;a href="http://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/" target="_blank"&gt;HCUP Nationwide Inpatient Sample&lt;/a&gt; (NIS), 2011, Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality (AHRQ).&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Total of all counties in this Website&lt;/b&gt;: Numbers are presented for all counties included in this Website.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Counties&lt;/b&gt;: Previously chosen counties are listed. You can select a specific region for more detailed results. Detailed results include characteristics for each region (age, gender, payer, and race).&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Number of discharges&lt;/b&gt;: The number of hospital stays (or discharges) for the selected condition or procedure is provided for each region.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Rate of discharges&lt;/b&gt;: The number of hospital stays (or discharges) divided by the number of residents in the region. region resident or population numbers are obtained from the US Census Bureau.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Mean costs in dollars&lt;/b&gt;: The mean or average cost is sometimes reported for each region. Costs are the actual value of these services (while charges are what a hospital asks to be paid for services). Total charges were converted to costs using &lt;a href="http://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/db/state/costtocharge.jsp" target="_blank"&gt;cost-to-charge ratios&lt;/a&gt; based on hospital accounting reports from the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS). In general, costs are less than charges.  AHRQ adjusts the &lt;a href="http://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/db/state/costtocharge.jsp" target="_blank"&gt;cost-to-charge ratios&lt;/a&gt; to work with this type of hospital data.&lt;/p&gt;	&lt;p&gt;If you select a specific region you will get following:&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Age group&lt;/b&gt;: Patient age in years is based on the admission date to the hospital and date of birth. The number of stays in each age group is reported.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Gender&lt;/b&gt;: The number of males and females is reported for the selected region and condition or procedure.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Race&lt;/b&gt;: Race/ethnicity of the patient as listed in the medical record. Racial and ethnic categories are collapsed into larger groups based on US Census Bureau designations.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;You may notice some special codes in the tables:&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Not enough data&lt;/b&gt;: When there are not enough data to report a value, a dash appears.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Small number suppression&lt;/b&gt;: Small raw numbers may be suppressed to protect patient confidentiality. In this case, a &amp;quot;c&amp;quot; appears.&lt;/p&gt;</InterpretationText><ReportAttributes>DRGsDischargesFilters</ReportAttributes><IconSets /><Filters><Filter Type="DRGsDischarges"><Values><FilterValue Name="Major Diagnosis Category" /><FilterValue Name="Diagnosis Related Group" /><FilterValue Name="Health Condition or Topic" /><FilterValue Name="Procedure" /></Values></Filter></Filters><Datasets><Dataset Name="Inpatient Discharge" /></Datasets><Columns><Column Id="0" Name="Number of discharges" IsMeasure="false"><IsChanged>true</IsChanged><IsDeleted>false</IsDeleted><SkipAudit>false</SkipAudit></Column><Column Id="0" Name="Mean cost in dollars" IsMeasure="false"><IsChanged>true</IsChanged><IsDeleted>false</IsDeleted><SkipAudit>false</SkipAudit></Column><Column Id="0" Name="Rate of Discharges Per 1000 Persons" IsMeasure="false"><IsChanged>true</IsChanged><IsDeleted>false</IsDeleted><SkipAudit>false</SkipAudit></Column></Columns><Footer>&lt;p&gt; * Weighted national estimates from HCUP Nationwide Inpatient Sample (NIS), 2009, Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality (AHRQ), based on data collected by individual States and provided to AHRQ by the States. Total number of weighted discharges in the U.S. based on HCUP NIS = 39,434,956. Statistics based on estimates with a relative standard error (standard error / weighted estimate) greater than 0.30 or with standard error = 0 are not reliable, and are designated with a †.&lt;br/&gt;** All statistics are unadjusted.
	&lt;/p&gt;</Footer></ReportManifest>"'),
